room_title: Escape room "Tyrannosolveus Rex" by Surelocked In in Frederick
room_description:
When something went wrong at the dig site, you were their first call. Your mission: investigate the site and make things right. Your reward: enough cash to shock a stegosaurus. Seems simple enough, even if they keep insisting that it's too dangerous to leave the compound after dark...
It's an hour before sundown, but how scary can a bunch of ancient fossils be?
